text: Sofia El Marikh ( Moroccan pronunciation: ; born ), also spelled Sophia El Mareekh, is a musician and entertainer from Casablanca, Morocco.https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2013/09/104176/moroccan-sofia-el- marikh-named-one-of-the-most-beautiful-women-in-the- world/http://waleg.com/archives/026742.htmlhttp://waleg.com/archives/024341.html She was a contestant on Star Academy I. == Discography == === Albums === * Kelmet Hobb 2007 * Tahwak 2011 === Singles === * Tahwak (She Adores You) * Nmout 3lik (I Love You till Death) * Es'alni Ana (Ask Me) * Bezzaf Bezaf (a lot, a lot) * Baheb Feek (What I Love about You) * Kelmet Hobb (Word of Love) == Videography == * "Tahwak" – Wissam Smayra * "Es'alni Ana" – Wissam Smayra * "Baheb Feek" – Randa Alam * "Kelmet hobb" – Laila Kanaan == References == == Social Media == * Facebook Category:1981 births Category:Living people Category:People from Casablanca Category:Moroccan female singers Category:Singers who perform in Classical Arabic Category:Contestants from Arabic singing competitions Category:21st-century women singers
